# Eficodeweatherapp

## Overview
Eficode weatherapp

## Table of Contents

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Testing](#testing)

## Installation

-Backend
Install backend dependencies:
npm install
Start the backend server:
npm starta

Frontend
Install frontend dependencies:
npm install
Start the frontend application:
npm start

Running Tests

-Backend
To run backend tests:
npm test

Frontend
To run frontend tests:
npm test

Notes:
Ensure Node.js and npm are installed on your machine before running the installation commands.

## Usage
Key Features:
1. Real-time Weather Updates
WeatherApp fetches real-time weather data from OpenWeatherMap

2. Location-based Forecast
The application allows users to view the current weather for a predefined location

3. Docker
WeatherApp is Dockerized

4. Test Automation
The application is equipped with automated tests using Mocha for unit testing and Robot Framework for integration testing.

## Testing
Unit tests for WeatherApp are located in the test directory. 

## Automated Tests
WeatherApp includes automated tests using Robot Framework.
